Apple CEO Tim Cook holds an iPad during a presentation at Apple headquarters in Cupertino, California October 16, 2014 Robert Galbraith/Reuters Apple is hosting an event today that could see the introduction of an iPad Pro, a device aimed at those who want to use an iPad to work. In order to cater to this market, many consider that a stylus-type device is essential — an idea backed up by Microsoft's Surface Pro line.
